<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-02-25T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-02-25T07:00:00-05:00" n="44" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d44">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/19741:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Finland</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Schoenfeld</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Helsinki</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-02-25T14:00:00+02:00">February
                                    25, 1942—2 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 3:03 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>149. My telegram no. 147, today.<note n="60" xml:id="d44fn60">Not
                                printed.</note> It is now quite obvious that the Finnish Government
                            is following a deliberate policy of suppressing or at least distorting
                            all statements by President Roosevelt bearing on the war situation. This
                            contrasts even with policy toward Great Britain as Churchill’s
                            pronouncements are reported in the Finnish press in some detail. I am
                            somewhat at a loss to know what we can do about this in view of manifest
                            control over Finnish press exercised by Germans and should welcome the
                            opinion of the Department as to any action that might be taken.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Schoenfeld</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>